726167f-a.text:
Borden Avenue, north side, east from 5th Street. On the corner is the yard of the Arthur Johnson Corporation, contractors, the other buildings being old tenements. On the left is the spire of St. Mary's Roman Catholic Church and on the extreme right the Vernon Boulevard viaduct..
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936

726168f-a.text:
Borden Avenue, at the N.W. corner of 5th Street, showing the Long Island Railroad branch of the Y.M.C.A. Across the roof of the building are the stacks of the Pennsylvania Railroad power house.
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936

726169f-b.text:
Borden Avenue, west from 5th Street, toward the East River. The first building on the right is the Long Island Railroad branch of the Y.M.C.A. On the south side of the avenue (left) are the yards of the Long Island Railroad. The Empire State
Building appears in views 1 and 3.
P. L. Sperr  October 25, 1936
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2,3
